                    <h1 class="fbcms_content fbcms_replacementcontent fbcms_plaintext inside_title" id="content_152865">Coronavirus Updates and Resource Page</h1>
                    <div class="fbcms_content fbcms_richtext inside_center" id="content_152866">
    <div class="fbcms_richtext_content">
        <p>L'Anse Creuse Community,</p>

<p>On April 2, 2020 Gov. Gretchen Whitmer announced the closure of all K-12 schools for face-to-face teaching for the remainder of the school year to prevent the spread of the coronavirus.  We will continue to communicate updates and information during this unprecedented time through email and posting on this webpage.</p>

<p>Thank you for your understanding and continued support.</p>
    </div>
</div>
<div class="fbcms_content fbcms_richtext inside_center" id="content_152867">
    <div class="fbcms_richtext_content">
        <h2>Coronavirus Communication and information</h2>

<p><img alt="food logo" class="Left_Align_With_Padding" src="/downloads/supts_page/new_food_logo.png" style="height:163px; width:200px">In an effort to support our families and the greater community during the school closure, the district will be providing free healthy meals for kids throughout the community until the end of the school year.   Please click flyer below with locations and times for food pick up and also local food pantry resources for the community.</p>

<p><a href="/downloads/supts_page/free_healthy_meals_for_kids_flyer.pdf" target="_blank">Free Healthy Meals for Kids Distribution &amp; Food Pantry Resources</a></p>

<h6>District Communication from the Superintendent:</h6>

<p>A district update from the Superintendent on April 17, 2020.<br><a href="/downloads/supts_page/district_update_4.17.20_learning_plans.pdf" target="_blank">4.17.20 District Update</a><br><br>
A district update from the Superintendent on April 2, 2020.<br><a href="/downloads/supts_page/district_update_4.2.20_on_letterhead.pdf" target="_blank">4.2.20 District Update</a></p>

<p>A district update from the Superintendent on March 23, 2020.<br><a href="/downloads/32320_mtg/3.23.20_district_update.pdf" target="_blank">3.23.20 District Update</a></p>

<p>A district update from the Superintendent on March 18, 2020.<br><a href="/downloads/supts_page/district_update_-_march_18.pdf" target="_blank">3.18.20 District Update</a></p>

<p>A message from the Superintendent regarding the closure of all public schools on March 13, 2020.<br><a href="/downloads/supts_page/coronavirus_communication_3.13.20_closing_school.pdf" target="_blank">3.13.20 Coronavirus Communication</a></p>

<p>A message from the Superintendent with an update on the <span>Coronavirus on March 12, 2020.</span><br><a href="/downloads/supts_page/coronavirus_communication_3.12.20.pdf" target="_blank">3.12.20 <span>Coronavirus</span> Communication</a></p>

<p>A message from the Superintendent regarding news coverage and C<span>oronavirus</span> on March 6, 2020.<br><a href="/downloads/supts_page/coronavirus_letter_3.6.20.pdf" target="_blank">3.6.20 <span>Coronavirus</span> Communication</a></p>

<h2>Educational &amp; emotional resources for Students and community </h2>

<p><strong>EDUCATIONAL RESOURCES FOR STUDENTS K-12</strong></p>

<p>Please click on the link below for online educational resources for K-12 students during this time of school closures.  This page will be updated regularly.  Also, please check your individual building media center pages for websites and subscriptions that may be unique to your school.</p>

<p><a href="http://www.lc-ps.org/for-students/" target="_blank">Student Online Educational Resources Page</a></p>

<p><strong>SOCIAL-EMOTIONAL SUPPORT AND COMMUNITY RESOURCES</strong></p>

<p>Please click on the links below for assistance and support resources for emotional needs, food assistance, and social and emotional skills to help children and community members during this difficult time.</p>

<p><a href="/downloads/supts_page/macomb_county_covid_19_resources.pdf" target="_blank">Macomb County COVID 19 Resources</a> (information related to: physical &amp; mental health, unemployment, housing/energy/food/water assistance, financial relief, transportation, internet &amp; cell phone services)</p>

<p><a href="http://childmind.org/coping-during-covid-19-resources-for-parents/" target="_blank">Supporting Families During COVID-19 </a>(Community Resource)<br><a href="http://childmind.org/enfrentar-el-covid-19-recursos-para-padres/" target="_blank">Enfrentar el COVID-19:recursos para padres</a> (Spanish Community Resource)<br><a href="http://connection.misd.net/" target="_blank">The Right Connection in Macomb County</a> (Community Resource)<br><a href="http://www.nasponline.org/resources-and-publications/resources-and-podcasts/school-climate-safety-and-crisis/health-crisis-resources/talking-to-children-about-covid-19-(coronavirus)-a-parent-resource" target="_blank">National Association of School Psychologist Parent Resource</a> (Talking to Kids about Coronavirus)<br><a href="http://mca.macombgov.org/sites/default/files/content/government/cha/emegency%20food%20flyer%209-19-19.pdf" target="_blank">Emergency Food Assistance Resource</a><br><a href="http://starr.org/covid-19-school-cancellation-and-trauma/" target="_blank">Coronavirus, School Cancellation and Trauma</a><br><a href="http://www.centervention.com/social-emotional-learning-activities/" target="_blank">Elementary and Middle School Social-Emotional Skills</a><br><a href="/downloads/supts_page/aop_flyer_2020.pdf" target="_blank">Adolescent Outreach Program - Telehealth Sessions During COVID-19 </a>(Macomb Family Services)<br><a href="http://everfi.com/partners/k-12-educators/social-emotional-learning/" target="_blank">Community Matters: K-12 Social &amp; Emotional Learning Courses</a></p>
